IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The Organization is devoted to the glorification of God through a unique ministry of music; performing musical concerts, producing and selling compact disks and broadcasting a weekly radio program - all with a focus on worship.
IRS990.MissionDesc: The Organization is devoted to the glorification of God through a unique ministry of music; performing musical concerts, producing and selling compact disks and broadcasting a weekly program nationally and internationally - all with a focus on worship.
IRS990.Desc: During the year ended 8/31/23 The National Christian Choir performed for thousands of attendees at 12 concerts in the Maryland and Pennsylvania areas. The Choir arranged, performed, recorded and produced Christian music on CD's for sale in fulfillment of its mission of Christian ministry through music. The Choir also recorded and produced a radio concert program as part of its music ministry to radio audiences.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Business Administrator and Treasurer review the Annual Financial Statements and related Form 990 and present their findings to the Finance Subcomittee (comprised of independent board members) of the Board of Directors. Finally, the Treasurer's report, referencing the Financial Statements and Form 990, is presented to the board for approval and acceptance.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Annual compensation for the Director of Ministries and Music (the only compensated officer) is deliberated by the personnel committee, forwarded to the finance committee for review and approval, and finally approved by the entire independent board.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization maintains a copy of its application for recognition of exemption, its reviewed financial statements and its Form 990 for the past three years at its headquarters. These copies are available for public inspection.

Schedule L - Part IV - Business Transactions Involving Interested PersonsDirector and Treasurer John Dallavalle is the owner of Frederick Financial Planners, Inc., the firm that manages the Organization's investment accounts. Mr. Dallavalle does not receive any fee, payment, benefit or other compensation directly from the Organization. His firm receives the normal customary 0.8% investment fee from the Organization as it would from any other investment customer. This fee is less than the investment fee charged to the Organizaton by Morgan Stanley, the investment firm that previously managed the Organization's investments.Schedule O - Description of Services Provided by VolunteersAll Choir Members audition to become a member of the Choir.
